Grip
----

Grip â‰ˆ git

We'll have a look at how git and the reference implementation do things

- what is in .git? (grip-init)

  grip-init creates .grip (and whatever you want inside)
  reference implementation uses git (see .grip/.reference)
  you can do whatever you want in .grip

- what is the index? (grip-add)

  grip's "copy" of your files
  may differ from the actual files
  only updated when you run grip-add/grip-reset/grip-checkout

- what is a commit? (grip-commit)

  commits are snapshots of the index
  grip-commit creates commits

How to work with files in python? shutil, os
